Ethekwini Mayor, Zandile Gumede, says she won't resign as Mayor, but she'll abide by the ANC KwaZulu-Natal Executive Committee decision that she take a month-long leave of absence. She spoke to eNCA's Siphamandla Goge. JOHANNESBURG - Ethekwini Mayor, Zandile Gumede, says she won't resign as Mayor, but she'll abide by the ANC KwaZulu-Natal Executive Committee decision that she take a month-long leave of absence. She's been under pressure to step aside, pending the outcome of her fraud and corruption case. READ: Gumede's fate to be decided this weekend Gumede's currently out on bail with strict conditions attached. The party's PEC has been meeting in Empangeni this weekend to discuss the Durban Mayors future, among other issues. READ: eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede out on bail The body on Saturday reminded Gumede of the party's policy that those charged need to temporarily step aside.